# meta-dashboard

This Yocto layer provides recipes for a modern automotive dashboard application built with Qt 6.

## Features
- **Dashboard Application**: A Qt Quick / QML based dashboard UI.
- **Simulation**: Python scripts for simulating CAN/vcan data for testing.
- **Custom Image**: A ready-to-use image recipe (`dashboard-image`) that includes all necessary components.

## Dependencies

This layer depends on:

- **URI**: git://git.yoctoproject.org/poky
  - **branch**: scarthgap
- **URI**: git://github.com/meta-qt6/meta-qt6
  - **branch**: scarthgap

## Installation

To add this layer to your build environment, run:

```bash
bitbake-layers add-layer meta-dashboard
```

## Included Recipes

### recipes-dashboard/dashboard-app
The main C++ and QML dashboard application.
- Installs the binary to `/usr/bin/dashboard-app`.
- Includes a vcan setup script at `/usr/bin/setup-vcan`.
- Includes simulation scripts at `/usr/share/dashboard/sim`.

### recipes-core/images/dashboard-image.bb
A core image with Qt 6 and the dashboard app pre-installed.

## Usage
Once the layer is added, you can build the dashboard image:

```bash
bitbake dashboard-image
```

